<br>
When I first saw the details of the original mod rod2 I couldn't quite believe it. Magicians could actually summon mana! Too weird. I tried to justify it in fantasy world terms by noting that the relatively small amount of mana that we're able to summon cost quite a lot of health to actually use. Perhaps that doesn't make sense, so let me try again. Mod rod2 requires 400 mana (book value) to cast and it summons one rod. The rod gives 660 mana at a cost of 900 health. Therefore a magician could effectively summon  260 mana. As long as their health didn't give out magicians could summon mana as fast as they could cast spells. Which we do frequently, with the help of a healer (and we can replenish the healer's mana far faster than our own). To me, it seemed weird that anyone could summon mana. But why complain, eh?<br>
<br>
Now, I'm simply becoming resigned to having the weirdness removed. My biggest complaint is that a person can only use one rod per minute. That has to change. I have no faith that VI will be able to retune the high-end encounters effectively in any reasonable time frame. They will have so many PoP problems to attend to that the imbalance introduced by the 1 minute rule won't get fixed.<br>
<br>
It semms to me that I have to relearn how to raid. &quot;Everything you know is wrong.&quot; Well, maybe not. Pets are still going to less useful than intended, at least for me. I don't bother with pets against AoE mobs. Gues what's in ToV? I'm looking forward to the new planes, though. All those new spells against summoned creatures suggest that at least some of the planes will have places where magicians can really shine. <p><p align=center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=237657><b>Enheduanna Lia</b></a>, Arch Mage<br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1113<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/10/02 12:51:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1516.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Uh Yiar ..</span><hr size=1> .. most monks in raid guilds at 60 have over 1400 AC.  My monk hit 1100 back around 55 pre-vellious.  The barrier to monk tanking is not AC, it's HP.  Once get your monk to about 3700 HP unbuffed, you can start being a tank; 4k is the dream HP mark for unbuffed monks.  Most 60 monks have AC coming out their ears.  They're well past the 1250-1300 soft AC cap.  This is why I think an AC nerf won't hurt monks much now.  It will just adjust things for the future when more AC will matter.  The &quot;cap&quot; is soft and varies with the MOB.<br>
<br>
BTW, the comment about 7500 hp was for unbuffed warriors.  That's about 9500 buffed.  A 9k (buffed) warrior is not all that uncommon at the high end.  That's about what you need to start thinking about being able to do AoW.  You need 3 or 4 of those to start thinking about doing Emporer.  The CH nerf will indeed be a nerf for existing play at the high end. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1516.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1516.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1516.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.threadControl?topicID=1516.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1516.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1516.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionavief